==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spick
<hw>Spick</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Sw.
<ets>spik</ets>. See <er>Spike</er> a nail.]</ety> <def>A spike or
nail.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Spick and span</b></col>, <cd>quite new; that is, as new
as a spike or nail just made and a chip just split; brand-new; as, a
<xex>spick and span</xex> novelty. See <er>Span-new</er>.</cd></cs> <--
now hypehnated, and more commonly meaning spotlessly clean -->
<rj><au>Howell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spicknel</ent>⟦br⟧
